  "prompt": "What is an organized knowledge structure reflecting on one's past experience and future expectations called?",
  "response": "An organized knowledge structure reflecting on one's past experience and future expectations is typically known as a \"schema.\" Schemas are cognitive frameworks that help individuals organize and interpret information based on prior experiences, beliefs, and expectations. They guide perception, memory, and behavior by providing a structured understanding of complex information.",
